A pole, a ball saved on the line, a bar and ... Finally the goal! Traveling on the pitch of Red Star Belgrade on Wednesday night in the Champions League, Spurs Tottenham have resumed four times to open the score (34th, 0-1). After the unfortunate Harry Kane and Heung-Min Son, it was finally Giovani Lo Celso that triggered the wide success of Londoners in Serbia (0-4). A goal totally WTF, worthy of the video game FIFA!
